Hello, this is 6-minute English from BBCLearningEnglish. I'm Phil

4
00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
And I'm Beth. Phil, what makes home special for you?

5
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
Maybe it's sleeping in your own bed. The view from the window

6
00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:25.000
or a loved family pet. What makes you feel like your home, Phil?

7
00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:29.000
You know what, I think it's just relaxing on my sofa in my living room.

8
00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:31.000
Very nice.

9
00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:35.000
Well, you might not realize it, but for your brain, one of the strongest

10
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:39.000
identifiers of home is smell. Listen, as BBC presents

11
00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:43.000
as Monty Chesterton and Tristan Arton, describe the smell

12
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:47.000
which give them the feeling of home. My granddad's house,

13
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:51.000
smell of pine and damp and mossy books.

14
00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:55.000
I know my mom's perfume, my dad's preferred soap.

15
00:00:55.000 --> 00:00:59.000
This program will be finding out why our sense of smell is so

16
00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:03.000
important to feeling at home, even when we don't notice it.

17
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.000
As always, we'll be introducing some useful new vocabulary

